link:labelLink.link:label: Reporting Date Offset
This dimension is used to report information based on an offset period relative to the reporting date.
RD Minus 12M

The date(s) relating to the reported information is/are exactly 12 months prior to the date(s) of the reporting period.
For example, where the reporting date is 30 June XXX1, the information reported is as at 30 June XXX0.
Where the reporting period is 1 January XXX1 to 30 June XXX1, the information reported relates to the period 1 January XXX0 to 30 June XXX0.
RD Minus 18M

The date(s) relating to the reported information is/are exactly 18 months prior to the date(s) of the reporting period.
For example, where the reporting date is 30 June XXX2, the information reported is as at 31 December XXX0.
Where the reporting period is 1 January XXX2 to 30 June XXX2, the information reported relates to the period 1 July XXX0 to 31 December XXX0.
RD Minus 24M

The date(s) relating to the reported information is/are exactly 24 months prior to the date(s) of the reporting period.
For example, where the reporting date is 30 June XXX2, the information reported is as at 30 June XXX0.
Where the reporting period is 1 January XXX2 to 30 June XXX2, the information reported relates to the period 1 January XXX0 to 30 June XXX0.
RD Minus 30M

The date(s) relating to the reported information is/are exactly 30 months prior to the date(s) of the reporting period.
For example, where the reporting date is 30 June XXX3, the information reported is as at 31 December XXX0.
Where the reporting period is 1 January XXX3 to 30 June XXX3, the information reported relates to the period 1 July XXX0 to 31 December XXX0.
RD Minus 6M

The date(s) relating to the reported information is/are exactly 6 months prior to the date(s) of the reporting period.
For example, where the reporting date is 30 June XXX1, the information reported is as at 31 December XXX0.
Where the reporting period is 1 January XXX1 to 30 June XXX1, the information reported relates to the period 1 July XXX0 to 31 December XXX0.
